  "response": "To upgrade from Android 4.4.2 (KitKat) to Android 6.0 (Marshmallow), you'll need to consider several factors:\n\n1. Device Compatibility\n- Check if your specific device model supports Marshmallow\n- Not all devices from the KitKat era can be upgraded\n\n2. Upgrade Methods:\na) Official OTA Update\n- Check Settings > About phone > System updates\n- If available, download and install directly\n\nb) Manufacturer's Website\n- Visit your phone manufacturer's website\n- Check for official firmware updates\n- Download and install manually\n\nc) Custom ROM (Advanced users)\n- Install a custom Marshmallow-based ROM\n- Requires:\n  * Unlocked bootloader\n  * Root access\n  * Technical knowledge\n  * Potential warranty voiding\n\n3. Recommended Steps:\n- Backup all data\n- Ensure sufficient battery charge\n- Connect to stable Wi-Fi\n- Have sufficient storage space\n- Follow manufacturer's specific instructions\n\n4. Potential Limitations\n- Older devices might have performance issues\n- Some features might not work perfectly\n- Consider device age and hardware capabilities\n\nIf unsure, consult your device manufacturer or a professional technician for specific guidance.",
